<br>
All input is appreciated.<br>
<br>
Gath Wolvesbane<br>
35th lvl Warrior Crimson Fury<br>
Saryrn<br>
<br>
I know, 35th lvl is a little low to concern myself with such things but its better to start collecting equipment now rather than later.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukaluianismyname.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaluian is my name</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/20/00 11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hrmmr</span><hr size=1> For dragons, go with a mix of MR and CR/FR.  Wolfs Eye jewelry gives a nice boost to MR, as does Mithril Armor.  Try to get ahold of a Gnomish Environment Suit, and DEFINITELY a Crown of the Froglok Kings.  If you can get both your MR and CR/FR up to 70 or so unbuffed, you're in good shape.  With CR/FR buffs, that'll rocket higher, and if you have a bard in your group twisting elemental + guardian, then they'll be astronomical.  If the bard has a good drum (MM-Tamourine-Selo's) It helps even more.<br>
<br>
For planes, stick with AC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ukhama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khama</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/20/00 3:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WAR - Gear on raids?</span><hr size=1> On dragon raids stick with fire/cold resist gear depending what dragon it is. Trust me it helps out alot. By me being a troll I naturally have a low fire resistance and my first Naggy run I was without fire gear and I dropped so fast. Next time I got resist gear and I survived it. So resist gear makes a huge difference.<br>
<br>
Any other time stick with AC. I can't stress how much AC is important to warriors. I sacrificed strenght items to get better AC items. Tanks primary purpose is it absorb damage not deal it and that is where is AC comes in escpecially in the planes. I'm working up on my AC is is good bit not where I want it to be.<br>
<br>
