<br>
Bard (Myself)<br>
Druid<br>
Cleric<br>
Ench<br>
Tank 1<br>
Tank 2<br>
<br>
As you can see, there's not much in the way of damage-dealing here.  The druid's job is to evac (I hunt primarily in Sebilis), keep us thorned, dot, etc.  She does some fair damage, but not all *that* much.  As anyone who has ever fought with a bard knows, we're not exactly the masters of damage output- my functions include typical bard songs, as well as crowd control if no ench is available (A Leperous Scarab Says &quot;My Master is Kaluian&quot;)  (Your Charm Spell has worn off) (A Leperous Scarab says &quot;You will not evade me Kaluian&quot;).  Ench does... duh... Crowd Control, haste buffing, etc etc.  Cleric (another big duh) heals.  So what does that leave us with?  Tank 1 and Tank 2.  Typically, the tanks I wind up with are very nicely equipped- just the fact that most people who hunt in Sebilis are well equipped.  I don't think I've been in a group in the last 4 or 5 weeks which was lacking quality tank equipment- whether the damage be coming through Staves of Shielding, Fiery Avengers, Dragon Haste, Sebilis Haste, or whatever, the tanks I wind up with dish out a killing.  Basically, everyone else just supports them... the game is changing.  Grouping with a Mage or Necro is my nightmare (I hate pets).  A wizard isn't bad, but I'd rather have a druid.  The cleric and enchanter are indispensable, as is the bard (otherwise I don't have a group).  This leaves 2 slots open for variation, and one of them has to be a tank- and if it's not a war/pal/sk, then the other one most certainly has to be a tank as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulorddenkoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Denkoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/21/00 10:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/isengard_eq/Denkoo_files/Shag.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Strange...</span><hr size=1> Gath, <br>
<br>
 On dragon runs it is most important to keep your resistance up. If you are fighting Vox you need to worry about cold and magic resistance. Nag is fire and magic. Both resistances should be close to, if not over, 100 pre buffed. This is not easy to do, but is doable. You will need to sacrifice some ac to make it happen. Keep in mind as a tank you will be meleeing the dragon and they hit for some serious damage. Try not to give up to much AC in your quest for resistance. Main thing is not to get feared. If people get feared then you are in trouble. Harder to fight when you have 30 people there and 10 are feared at any given time. Anyways, I hope this helps some.<br>
<br>
